<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<exercise xml:id="exercise-images-and-pre-images" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>
    Images and pre-images
  </title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Let <m> f_{ 4 } \colon \set{ 1 , 2 } \to \set{ \mathrm{ red } , \mathrm{ blue } } </m> be the map from <m> \set{ 1 , 2 } </m> to <m> \set{ \mathrm{ red } , \mathrm{ blue } } </m> defined in (2) of <xref provisional="example-maps"/>; that is,
      
      <md>
        f_{ 4 } = \set{ \of{ 1 , \mathrm{ blue } } , \of{ 2 , \mathrm{ blue } } }
      </md>.
      
      Compute the given images and pre-images. Express your answer in roster notation.
    </p>
  </introduction>
  
  <task>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Compute the images <m> f_{ 4 } \of{ 1 } </m> and <m> f_{ 4 } \of{ 2 } </m>.
      </p>
    </statement>
    
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m> f_{ 4 } \of{ 1 } = f_{ 4 } \of{ 2 } = \mathrm{ blue } </m>.
      </p>
    </answer>
    
    <solution>
      <p>
        Since <m> \of{ 1 , \mathrm{ blue } } \in f_{ 4 } </m>, the image <m> f_{ 4 } \of{ 1 } </m> of <m> 1 </m> under <m> f_{ 4 } </m> is
        
        <md>
          f_{ 4 } \of{ 1 } = \mathrm{ blue }
        </md>.
        
        Similarly, since <m> \of{ 2 , \mathrm{ blue } } \in f_{ 4 } </m>, the image <m> f_{ 4 } \of{ 2 } </m> of <m> 2 </m> under <m> f_{ 4 } </m> is
        
        <md>
          f_{ 4 } \of{ 2 } = \mathrm{ blue }
        </md>.
      </p>
    </solution>
  </task>
  
  <task>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Compute the image <m> \im \of{ f_{ 4 } } </m>.
      </p>
    </statement>
    
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m> \im \of{ f_{ 4 } } = \set{ \mathrm{ blue } } </m>.
      </p>
    </answer>
    
    <solution>
      <p>
        Since <m> f_{ 4 } \of{ x } = \mathrm{ blue } </m> for all <m> x \in \set{ 1 , 2 } </m>, the image <m> \im \of{ f_{ 4 } } </m> of <m> f_{ 4 } </m> is
        
        <md>
          \im \of{ f_{ 4 } } = f_{ 4 } \of{ \set{ 1 , 2 } } = \set{ \mathrm{ blue } }
        </md>.
      </p>
    </solution>
  </task>
  
  <task>
    <statement>
      <p>
        Compute the pre-images <m> f_{ 4 }^{ -1 } \of{ \mathrm{ red } } </m> and <m> f_{ 4 }^{ -1 } \of{ \mathrm{ blue } } </m>.
      </p>
    </statement>
    
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m> f_{ 4 }^{ -1 } \of{ \mathrm{ red } } = \emptyset </m> and <m> f_{ 4 }^{ -1 } \of{ \mathrm{ blue } } = \set{ 1 , 2 } </m>.
      </p>
    </answer>
    
    <solution>
      <p>
        Since <m> f_{ 4 } \of{ x } = \mathrm{ blue } </m> for all <m> x \in \set{ 1 , 2 } </m>, the pre-images <m> f_{ 4 }^{ -1 } \of{ \mathrm{ red } } </m> and <m> f_{ 4 }^{ -1 } \of{ \mathrm{ blue } } </m> of <m> \mathrm{ red } </m> and <m> \mathrm{ blue } </m> under <m> f_{ 4 } </m> are
        
        <md>
          f_{ 4 }^{ -1 } \of{ \mathrm{ red } } = \setmid{ x \in \set{ 1 , 2 } }{ f_{ 4 } \of{ x } = \mathrm{ red } } = \emptyset
        </md>
        
        and
        
        <md>
          f_{ 4 }^{ -1 } \of{ \mathrm{ blue } } = \setmid{ x \in \set{ 1 , 2 } }{ f_{ 4 } \of{ x } = \mathrm{ blue } } = \set{ 1 , 2 }
        </md>.
      </p>
    </solution>
  </task>
</exercise>
